---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro'
import LegalPage from '@/components/LegalPage.astro'

const title = 'Privacy Policy - GK Vip Transfer Kos'
const description =
    'How GK Vip Transfer handles your data: booking details you send via WhatsApp, consent-based Google Analytics cookies, and your rights under GDPR.'
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} lang="en" pageType="legal">
  <LegalPage lang="en" heading="Privacy Policy" updated="12 July 2026" altHref="/el/privacy/">
    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      GK Vip Transfer is a family-run private transfer service on Kos island, Greece, operated by
      Georgia Kommata. For anything related to your personal data, contact us
      at <a data-email-user="gkommata" data-email-domain="gmail.com">gkommata [at] gmail [dot] com</a> or on WhatsApp at +30 697 296 1560.
    </p>

    <h2>What data we collect</h2>
    <p>
      This website has no user accounts and no server-side database. The booking form only collects
      your trip details: pickup and drop-off location, date, time, number of passengers, and vehicle
      choice. When you submit the form, those details are placed into a WhatsApp message that you
      send to us from your own WhatsApp account. At that point we also receive your WhatsApp profile
      name and phone number, exactly as with any WhatsApp conversation.
    </p>
    <p>
      We use this information solely to arrange and provide your transfer. We do not use it for
      marketing lists and we never sell it.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
    <p>
      With your consent, we use Google Analytics 4 to understand how visitors use the site (pages
      viewed, approximate location, device type). Analytics cookies are set only after you choose
      "Accept" in the cookie banner; if you decline, no analytics run at all. We use no advertising
      or marketing cookies.
    </p>
    <p>
      Google's processing is described in
      the <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
      Analytics data is retained for up to 14 months.
    </p>
    <p>
      <button
        id="reset-cookie-choice"
        class="text-sm font-medium underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent"
      >
        Change your cookie choice
      </button>
    </p>

    <h2>Legal bases</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Booking and providing your transfer: performance of a contract (GDPR Art. 6(1)(b)).</li>
      <li>Analytics cookies: your consent (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a)), which you can withdraw at any time.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who else processes your data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>WhatsApp (Meta Platforms) delivers your booking messages, under the <a href="https://www.whatsapp.com/legal/privacy-policy-eea" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">WhatsApp Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
      <li>Google processes analytics data if you consent, as described above.</li>
      <li>Our hosting and network providers (Netlify, Cloudflare) may process IP addresses in standard server logs for security and delivery of the site.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How long we keep your data</h2>
    <p>
      Booking conversations on WhatsApp are kept only as long as needed to provide the transfer and
      handle any follow-up, after which they can be deleted on request.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under the GDPR you can ask us for access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal data,
      restriction of or objection to its processing, and a portable copy.
      Email <a data-email-user="gkommata" data-email-domain="gmail.com">gkommata [at] gmail [dot] com</a> and we will respond as soon as
      possible. You can also lodge a complaint with the Hellenic Data Protection Authority
      (<a href="https://www.dpa.gr" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">dpa.gr</a>).
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      If we change how we handle personal data, we will update this page and the date at the top.
    </p>
  </LegalPage>

  <script is:inline data-astro-rerun>
    document.getElementById('reset-cookie-choice')?.addEventListener('click', function () {
      try { localStorage.removeItem('gk-cookie-consent'); } catch (e) {}
      location.reload();
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
